        "id": 2299981,
        "name": "Dale McClaran",
        "username": "Dale_McClaran",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dale_mcclaran/{size}/683_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-11-18T18:33:14.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=2670078\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2014 Domaine Pierre Gelin Fixin 1er Cru Clos Napoleon</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Fixin 1er Cru (11/18/2017)</em><br>\nNot decanted but opened 8 hrs. \u2013 served in a Riedel Pinot Extreme. Initial reaction was wow that is pretty legit Burg \u2013 great nose, full of wild raspberries, subtle smoky coal embers, and a very small sliver of barrel. Bright, spry, of and full of energy, undefined red fruits leave a very positive impression, seems more to come if given a few years sideways. Nice finish that leaves a slight saline taste. A really good deal at $28, and I bet you could find this for $25. <em><strong>(90 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" class=\"broken-image\" title=\"This image is broken\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-unlink svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#unlink\"></use></svg></span></p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
