      {
        "id": 2300722,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-11-20T08:40:11.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is a nice wine, and Gelin are really working pretty seriously these days. The wines are elegant and classy. Their old vines in the Gevrey Clos Prieur usually produce one of their best cuv\u00e9es. The Clos Napol\u00e9on tends to be quite dark fruity and wild aromatically and rather supple and gourmand on the palate - at least in my experience. I spent a couple of months living in Fixin on one occasion and would drop by quite often. They sometimes dig out oldish vintages of their Clos de B\u00e8ze for sale at the domaine.</p>",
